Adaro Energy, Benakat, Bumi Serpong: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-04-11T01:45:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/adaro-energy-benakat-bumi-serpong-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 0.3 percent to 3,741.81.  Energy companies: Crude oil for May delivery advanced 2.3
percent to $112.79 a barrel in  New York  on April 8, the highest
settlement since Sept. 22, 2008. The contract was at $112.73 a
barrel in after-hours trading as of 8:15 a.m. Jakarta time.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ), Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company, rose 0.9 percent to 2,850 rupiah. PT
Benakat Petroleum Energy (BIPI IJ) fell 1.2 percent to 86
rupiah.  Coal producers: Power-station coal  prices  at  Australia ’s
Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, increased 1.8 percent to
$123.30 a metric ton in the week ended April 8. PT Bumi
Resources (BUMI IJ),  Asia ’s biggest exporter of power-station
coal, slid 0.8 percent to 3,250 rupiah and PT Adaro Energy (ADRO
IJ),  Indonesia ’s second-largest coal producer, fell 1.1 percent
to 2,300 rupiah.  PT Bumi Serpong Damai (BSDE IJ): The property developer
expects 4 trillion rupiah ($463 million) of sales this year,
spurred by its BSD City project near Jakarta, Investor Daily
Indonesia reported, citing President Director Harry Budi
Hartanto. The company posted sales of 2.48 trillion rupiah in
2010, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. Bumi Serpong rose
1.2 percent to 860 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  